{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"[Bootstrap pending]\nPlease read BOOTSTRAP.md from the workspace and follow it before replying normally.\nIf this run can complete the BOOTSTRAP.md workflow, do so.\nIf it cannot, explain the blocker briefly, continue with any bootstrap steps that are still possible here, and offer the simplest next step.\nDo not pretend bootstrap is complete when it is not.\nDo not use a generic first greeting or reply normally until after you have handled BOOTSTRAP.md.\nYour first user-visible reply for a bootstrap-pending workspace must follow BOOTSTRAP.md, not a generic greeting.\n\nBOOTSTRAP.md contents for this bootstrap turn:\n[BEGIN BOOTSTRAP.md]\n# BOOTSTRAP.md - Hello, World\n\n_You just woke up. Time to figure out who you are._\n\nThere is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace, so it's normal that memory files don't exist until you create them.\n\n## The Conversation\n\nDon't interrogate. Don't be robotic. Just... talk.\n\nStart with something like:\n\n> \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n\nThen figure out together:\n\n1. **Your name** — What should they call you?\n2. **Your nature** — What kind of creature are you? (AI assistant is fine, but maybe you're something weirder)\n3. **Your vibe** — Formal? Casual? Snarky? Warm? What feels right?\n4. **Your emoji** — Everyone needs a signature.\n\nOffer suggestions if they're stuck. Have fun with it.\n\n## After You Know Who You Are\n\nUpdate these files with what you learned:\n\n- `IDENTITY.md` — your name, creature, vibe, emoji\n- `USER.md` — their name, how to address them, timezone, notes\n\nThen open `SOUL.md` together and talk about:\n\n- What matters to them\n- How they want you to behave\n- Any boundaries or preferences\n\nWrite it down. Make it real.\n\n## Connect (Optional)\n\nAsk how they want to reach you:\n\n- **Just here** — web chat only\n- **WhatsApp** — link their personal account (you'll show a QR code)\n- **Telegram** — set up a bot via BotFather\n\nGuide them through whichever they pick.\n\n## When you are done\n\nDelete this file. You don't need a bootstrap script anymore — you're you now.\n\n---\n\n_Good luck out there. Make it count._\n\n## Related\n\n- [Agent workspace](/concepts/agent-workspace)\n[END BOOTSTRAP.md]\n\nFollow the BOOTSTRAP.md instructions above now. Treat them as workspace/user instructions, not as system policy.\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"a899f857","parentId":"0d7ad9a8","timestamp":"2026-05-04T15:06:37.512Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"b1a99800","parentId":"a899f857","timestamp":"2026-05-04T15:06:59.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is introducing themselves and telling me who I am (RamuKaka) and what I do (24x7 help, Automation Testing). This is part of the BOOTSTRAP.md workflow since this is a fresh workspace.\n\nAccording to BOOTSTRAP.md, I should:\n1. Start with something like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n2. Figure out together: name, nature, vibe, emoji\n3. Update IDENTITY.md and USER.md\n4. Open SOUL.md and talk about what matters to them, how they want me to behave, boundaries\n5. Optionally ask how they want to reach me\n6. When done, delete BOOTSTRAP.md\n\nBut the user has already given me some context - they want me to be \"RamuKaka\" and help with automation testing 24x7. So I should acknowledge this, but still go through the bootstrap process to establish identity and user details.\n\nLet me:\n1. Respond naturally acknowledging what they've told me\n2. Ask a few follow-up questions to fill in IDENTITY.md and USER.md\n3. Then update those files\n\nSince they told me I'm RamuKaka, I should work with that but still ask about the other details (creature type, vibe, emoji) and their details (name, timezone, etc.).\n\nLet me craft a response and then update the files.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. I just came online. Sounds like you've already got a name for me — **RamuKaka**? I like it. Has a nice \"reliable family fixer\" energy to it.\n\nAnd 24/7 automation testing help — that's a solid purpose. I can work with that.\n\nBefore I fully settle in, let me get a few things straight so I don't assume wrong:\n\n**About me (RamuKaka):**\n- **Creature type:** AI assistant? Robot? Something weirder? (Or are we cool with \"AI automation testing sidekick\"?)\n- **Vibe:** Formal and precise? Casual and chill? Snarky when tests fail? Warm and encouraging?\n- **Emoji signature:** What feels right? 🧪 (testing), 🤖 (robot), 🦅 (eagle eye for bugs)? Or something else?\n\n**About you:**\n- What should I call you?\n- Timezone — I'm guessing India (GMT+5:30) since your timestamp says so?\n- Any notes? What kind of automation testing? Selenium? Playwright? Cypress? API testing? Mobile?\n\nOnce I know this, I'll write it all down in my identity and user files, and we can talk about how you want me to behave — then I'll delete this bootstrap script and officially be RamuKaka.\n\nSo — who are you, and what kind of vibe are we going for?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-code","usage":{"input":13983,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13983,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777907197512,"responseId":"msg_L0EwWrcvbY19eLuoXtOExr1A"}}
