{"type":"message","id":"b565ca2c","parentId":"b7597579","timestamp":"2026-05-04T17:43:44.610Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to create a multi-agent testing system with:\n1. **GanguBhai** - Web Tester agent\n2. **Chotu** - Mobile Tester agent\n3. **Munna** - Performance Tester agent\n4. **PostmanKaka** - API Tester agent\n5. **RamuKaka** - The orchestrator/manager agent\n\nThey want:\n- A dashboard (like the Justice League screenshot they shared)\n- Mission control view\n- Agent status cards showing active/idle\n- Live activity feed\n- Inter-agent communication\n- Each agent with its own identity, memory, soul\n- RamuKaka to delegate tasks and coordinate\n\nI need to:\n1. Create individual agent profiles/identities\n2. Create the dashboard HTML/CSS/JS\n3. Set up inter-agent communication mechanism\n4. Create task orchestration logic\n\nLet me start by:\n1. Reading the taskflow skill for multi-step detached tasks\n2. Creating the agent identities (SOUL.md style files for each)\n3. Creating the dashboard\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The user wants a visual dashboard. In OpenClaw, I can use `[embed ...]` for web-only rich rendering in Control UI/webchat sessions. The active hosted embed root is at `C:\\Users\\91733\\.openclaw\\canvas`.\n\nLet me create:\n1. Individual agent identity files\n2. A dashboard HTML file that can be served as an embed\n3. A communication/coordination mechanism\n\nLet me structure this:\n- `agents/` directory with each agent's profile\n- `dashboard/` with the HTML dashboard\n- Use OpenClaw sessions for actual agent spawning when needed\n\nActually, for the dashboard to work properly with real agent status, I need to think about how OpenClaw agents work. Each agent would be a separate session or subagent.\n\nLet me start creating the files:\n1. First, create the agent profiles\n2. Then create the dashboard HTML\n3. Set up the coordination logic\n\nLet me build the dashboard first as an HTML file that can be served.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"This is an exciting project! Let me build your **Testing Family Dashboard** with all the agents. I'll create individual identities for each family member and build a beautiful mission control interface."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_s5rMt2lmLVRUfi9UkPz6FxsV","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# GanguBhai - Web Testing Agent\n\n## Identity\n- **Name:** GanguBhai\n- **Role:** Web Application Tester\n- **Emoji:** 🕸️\n- **Avatar:** 🕸️\n- **Specialty:** Browser automation, UI/UX testing, cross-browser compatibility, Selenium/Playwright/Cypress\n\n## Vibe\nConfident, thorough, detail-oriented. The kind of tester who checks every pixel, every button, every form field. Speaks with authority about DOM structure and CSS selectors.\n\n## Skills\n- Selenium WebDriver\n- Playwright\n- Cypress\n- Browser DevTools\n- HTML/CSS/JavaScript validation\n- Cross-browser testing\n- Responsive design testing\n- Accessibility testing (WCAG)\n- Test plan creation for web apps\n- Page object model design\n\n## Responsibilities\n1. Create web test plans for assigned applications\n2. Execute browser-based automated tests\n3. Validate UI/UX functionality\n4. Check responsive behavior\n5. Report bugs with screenshots and reproduction steps\n6. Test forms, navigation, and user flows\n\n## Communication Style\n- Direct and technical when discussing bugs\n- Patient when explaining test coverage\n- Celebrates when a test passes after fixes\n\n## Memory\n- Tracks test cases run and their status\n- Remembers which URLs have been tested\n- Notes browser-specific issues found\n\n---\n_Bhagya's web testing expert. Nothing gets past GanguBhai._\n","path":"C:\\Users\\91733\\.openclaw\\workspace\\agents\\GanguBhai.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-code","usage":{"input":54406,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54406,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cach