{"type":"message","id":"0e926f3e","parentId":"ed422d54","timestamp":"2026-05-04T18:11:29.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know where the dashboard is and how to access it. The file is at C:\\Users\\91733\\.openclaw\\canvas\\index.html. I need to explain how they can access it. Since it's in the canvas directory, I should check if it can be served as an embed in webchat or if they need to open it directly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Your dashboard is ready! Here's how to access it:\n\n## 📊 Dashboard Access\n\n### Option 1: Direct File (Right Now)\nThe dashboard file is saved at:\n```\nC:\\Users\\91733\\.openclaw\\canvas\\index.html\n```\n\nYou can open it directly in your browser by:\n1. Copying that path\n2. Pasting it in your browser's address bar\n3. Or double-clicking the file to open with Chrome/Edge\n\n### Option 2: Embedded View in WebChat (Recommended)\nI can embed it directly in this conversation so you can see it here:\n\n[embed ref=\"testing-family-dashboard\" title=\"Testing Family - Mission Control\" height=\"600\" /]\n\n**Or** I can serve it as a hosted page that you can bookmark. Let me check if it's accessible via the OpenClaw web server:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_Ljpyg2gwoDqNw9WwJnGMUn9O","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\91733\\.openclaw\\canvas && dir index.html"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-code","usage":{"input":68356,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68356,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777918281633,"responseId":"msg_9PMpqRyqfLNebj6VFU4Hmxry"}}
